---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - The National Angle"
  description="What The National Angle covers, how it approaches uncertainty, and what readers should expect."
>
  <article class="infoPage">
    <header class="infoHero">
      <div class="signalPills"><span>About</span><span>Independent</span><span>Evidence-led</span></div>
      <h1>The Angle Behind the Headline</h1>
      <p class="pageDeck">The National Angle is an independent digital publication that goes beyond the event itself. We explain the forces, incentives, and consequences shaping important stories across world affairs, politics, business, technology, and incredible human stories.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="infoGrid">
      <section>
        <p class="cardLabel">01</p>
        <h2>What Readers Can Expect</h2>
        <p>We publish concise, accessible articles built around a clear question: what is the important angle that the headline alone does not explain? Each story aims to give readers useful context without unnecessary length or inflated certainty.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <p class="cardLabel">02</p>
        <h2>What Makes a National Angle Story</h2>
        <p>We look for consequential developments, surprising comparisons, overlooked incentives, and patterns that connect separate events. A compelling angle should deepen understanding, not distort the underlying facts.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <p class="cardLabel">03</p>
        <h2>Our Editorial Promise</h2>
        <p>We distinguish confirmed facts from interpretation, identify uncertainty when it matters, link useful evidence where practical, and correct material errors. Editorial coverage is not sold in exchange for favorable treatment.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="infoActions">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/">Read the reporting</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/method">See our method</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
